    <h3 class="about-section-title">What's the purpose of this app?</h3>
    <h4>We designed Eat Free to save you time and energy when it comes to weight loss. We have tools to calculate your personal calorie requirements depending on your desired weight loss rate. No more wondering what foods you can or cannot eat, by following the IIFYM (If It Fits Your Macros) strategy, you can eat whatever you want while losing weight! (Yes that includes junk food in moderate quantities)</h4>
    <h3 class="about-section-title">What is IIFYM?</h3>
    <h4><strong>If It Fits Your Macros</strong> is a diet strategy which the following approach: you can eat any foods you like, as long as it fits in your daily caloric budget and your daily macronutrient split (protein, carbohydrates, and fat). The gist of the idea is that if you eat oatmeal and whole wheat bread, the result (as far as body composition is concerned) is the same as if you were to eat the exact same amount of carbohydrates and fats from donuts, as long as calorie intake is equal and macronutrient targets are hit. According to this theory, gaining body fat is not about the types of foods you consume, rather the excess calories you are consuming.</h4>
    <h3 class="about-section-title">How does it work?</h3>
    <h4>By entering your physical stats the app will calculate your TDEE. Your TDEE (Total Daily Energy Expenditure) is an estimate of your maintenance level, that is, the amount of calories you must eat to maintain your current weight. From that as well as a desired weight loss rate that you specify, the app also calculates the maximum amount of calories you can consume per day to achieve said weight loss. From there the app provides a recipe list of various meals and snacks for you to build your meal plan from, ensuring that your daily calorie limit is not surpassed. A small lee-way of +50 calories is allowed provide ease of planning.</h4>

