    <h3 class="about-section-title">What are macros and why are they important?</h3>
    <h4>Macronutrients are what make up the caloric content of a food. Sometimes referred to as "macros" the three categories of macronutrients are carbohydrates, fat, and protein. The caloric combination of the macros is where the total number of calories comes from. In general, proteins and carbohydrates provide 4 calories per gram whereas fats provide 9 calories per gram. A good balance of macros is essential; a severe imbalance in any of the three macronutrients could lead to malnutrition and eventually long term health issues. </h4>
    <h3 class="about-section-title">How should I split my macros?</h3>
    <h4>There is no optimal macros split as everyone has different requirements. A professional athlete or bodybuilder will have significantly greater protein requirements than the average person with an interest in fitness. In addition, depending on what your goals are, (eg. weight loss, strength gains, mass gains, performance etc.) different splits may be more appropriate. That said, a well accepted starting place is the 40/40/20 split, a diet where 40% of your calories come from protein sources, 40% from carbohydrate sources and 20% from fat sources. The actual numbers can be adjusted over the course of the diet to meet your personal needs.</h4>
    <h3 class="about-section-title">How can I track my macros?</h3>
    <h4>Currently this app only tracks your macros composition on a day to day basis. Specifying a desired macros split and building meal plans that meet those macros is a feature that will be implemented in the future.</h4>
